casebody.data:
Ernest R. OLSEN, Appellant, v. SPARTA FOUNDRY COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellee. No. 7548. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 14, 1938. Maurice A. Barapcik and Joseph A. Struett, both of Chicago, 111., for appellant. McCobb & Heaney, of Grand Rapids, Mich., for appellee.

Before SIMONS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The court perceiving no abuse of discretion in the entry of an order by the District Judge dismissing the bill in the above cause, the order is hereby affirmed.
